@startuml Calculator Class Diagram

title Calculator Class Diagram

class Calculator {
    +add(a, b)
    +subtract(a, b)
    +multiply(a, b)
    +divide(a, b)
    +factorial(n: int): int
    +square(x: float): float
    +cube(x: float): float
    +square_root(x: float): float
    +cube_root(x: float): float
    +log10(x: float): float
    +ln(x: float): float
    +power(x: float, y: float): float
    +sin(x: float): float
    +cos(x: float): float
    +tan(x: float): float
    +asin(x: float): float
    +acos(x: float): float
    +atan(x: float): float
    +get_pi(): float
    +get_e(): float
}

enum Mode {
    NORMAL
    SCIENTIFIC
}

note top of Mode
    Module: src/session/mode.py
    Controls which operations are visible
    in the interactive session menu.
    parse_mode_command(input_str: str): Mode | None
    parses "mode normal" / "mode scientific" commands.
end note

class History {
    -_operations: list[str]
    +add_operation(operation_name: str, operands: list, result: float | int): None
    +get_all(): list[str]
    +save_to_file(filepath: str): None
    -_format_entry(operation_name: str, operands: list, result: float | int): str
}

note top of History
    Module: src/session/history.py
    Session-scoped operation tracker.
    Formats entries as operation(arg1, arg2, ...) = result.
    Persists to file on session end.
end note

class Logger {
    -_logger: logging.Logger
    +__init__(log_file: str = "error.log")
    +log_unsupported_operation(operation: str): None
    +log_invalid_operand(raw_value: str, expected_type: str): None
    +log_invalid_argument_count(operation: str, expected: int, given: int): None
    +log_division_by_zero(operands: list): None
    +log_domain_error(operation: str, error_message: str): None
}

note top of Logger
    Module: src/shared/logger.py
    Centralized file-based error logger.
    Appends plain-text lines to error.log.
    WARNING level: unsupported operations.
    ERROR level: coercion, arity, domain, divide-by-zero.
end note

note as OPERATIONS_NOTE
    <b>OPERATIONS</b> : dict[str, dict]
    Composed in src/operations/__init__.py
    from NORMAL_OPERATIONS (src/operations/normal.py)
    and SCIENTIFIC_OPERATIONS (src/operations/scientific.py).
    Maps operation keys to dispatch metadata:
    NORMAL: add, subtract, multiply, divide, power (arity=2)
    factorial (arity=1, coerce=int)
    square, cube, square_root, cube_root,
    log10, ln (arity=1, coerce=float)
    SCIENTIFIC: sin, cos, tan, asin, acos, atan (arity=1)
    pi, e (arity=0 — no operands needed)
    Each entry: { method, arity, label [, coerce] }
    Imported by session/input_handler.py and interface/cli.py.
end note

class OperationDispatcher {
    -_calculator: Calculator
    +__init__(calculator: Calculator)
    +coerce_operands(raw_args: list[str], coerce: Callable): list
    +dispatch(op_key: str, operands: list): float | int
}

note top of OperationDispatcher
    Module: src/shared/dispatcher.py
    Centralises operand coercion and method dispatch.
    Used by both InputHandler and CliDispatcher.
    No I/O or Logger dependency — callers handle errors.
end note

class BaseMode {
    +get_available_operations(mode: Mode): dict[str, dict]
    -_filter_operations_for_normal_mode(operations: dict): dict
}

note top of BaseMode
    Module: src/session/base_mode.py
    Shared mode-filtering logic composed by
    InputHandler and GuiCalculator.
    NORMAL: returns only NORMAL_OPERATIONS keys.
    SCIENTIFIC: returns full OPERATIONS dict.
end note

class InputHandler {
    -_calculator: Calculator
    -_input_fn: Callable[[str], str]
    -_history: History
    -_logger: Logger | None
    -_dispatcher: OperationDispatcher
    -_mode: Mode
    -_mode_handler: BaseMode
    +__init__(calculator: Calculator, input_fn: Callable | None, logger: Logger | None)
    +run(): None
    -_show_menu(): None
    -_get_available_operations_for_mode(): dict
    -_prompt_operands(arity: int, coerce: Callable): list
    -_dispatch(op_key: str, operands: list): float | int
}

note top of InputHandler
    Module: src/session/input_handler.py
    (shim: src/input_handler.py for backwards compat)
    Drives an interactive calculator REPL session.
    Re-exports OPERATIONS for backwards compatibility.
    _get_available_operations_for_mode() delegates to
    _mode_handler (BaseMode) for filtering logic.
end note

class GuiCalculator {
    -_root: tk.Tk
    -_calculator: Calculator
    -_logger: Logger | None
    -_dispatcher: OperationDispatcher
    -_history: History
    -_mode: Mode
    -_mode_handler: BaseMode
    -_result_label: tk.Label | None
    -_mode_toggle_btn: tk.Button | None
    -_btn_frame: tk.Frame | None
    -_history_text: tk.Text | None
    -_op_frame: tk.Frame | None
    +__init__(root: tk.Tk, calculator: Calculator, logger: Logger | None)
    +run(): None
    -_setup_layout(): None
    -_build_button_grid(): None
    -_rebuild_button_grid(): None
    -_get_button_colors(op_key: str): tuple[str, str, str]
    -_on_mode_toggle(): None
    -_on_mode_change(new_mode: Mode): None
    -_on_operation_click(op_key: str): None
    -_prompt_operands_dialog(op_key: str, arity: int, coerce: Callable): list | None
    -_execute_operation(op_key: str, operands: list): None
    -_update_result_display(result: float | int): None
    -_update_history_display(): None
    -_get_available_operations_for_mode(): dict
    -_show_error_dialog(title: str, message: str): None
}

note top of GuiCalculator
    Module: src/interface/gui.py
    iOS-style dark-themed Tkinter GUI.
    Mode toggle button (Normal/Scientific),
    4-column operation button grid with
    hover effects and orange accent for
    arithmetic operators.
    Result label (large right-aligned font).
    Module-level _THEME and _SYMBOL_MAP dicts
    control all colours and display labels.
    All calculation logic delegated to
    Calculator via OperationDispatcher.
    Mode filtering delegated to BaseMode.
    _on_mode_change / _history_text / _op_frame
    retained for API compatibility.
end note

note as RUN_SESSION_NOTE
    <b>run_session</b>(calculator: Calculator, input_fn: Callable | None, logger: Logger | None): None
    Free function in src/session/input_handler.py
    Convenience entry point: creates an InputHandler
    and calls handler.run()
end note

class CliDispatcher {
    -_calculator: Calculator
    -_logger: Logger | None
    -_dispatcher: OperationDispatcher
    +__init__(calculator: Calculator, logger: Logger | None)
    +dispatch_from_args(args: list[str]): int
    -_coerce_operands(raw_args: list[str], coerce: Callable): list
    -_dispatch(op_key: str, operands: list): float | int
    -_print_error(message: str): None
}

note top of CliDispatcher
    Module: src/interface/cli.py
    Parses CLI args, validates operands,
    dispatches to Calculator, prints result
    to stdout or error to stderr.
    Returns 0 on success, 1 on error.
end note

note as MAIN_NOTE
    <b>main()</b>
    Entry point in src/__main__.py
    Creates a Calculator instance.
    If "--gui" in sys.argv:
      imports GuiCalculator, creates tk.Tk root,
      instantiates GuiCalculator(root, calc), calls run().
    Otherwise (default CLI mode):
      calls run_session(calc).
    GuiCalculator import is conditional — only when --gui is used.
end note

OperationDispatcher --> Calculator : delegates calls to\n_calculator

InputHandler --> Calculator : holds reference via\n_calculator
InputHandler --> History : manages session history
InputHandler --> Logger : logs errors via\n_logger
InputHandler *-- OperationDispatcher : owns _dispatcher
InputHandler *-- BaseMode : owns _mode_handler
InputHandler ..> OPERATIONS_NOTE : reads registry for\nmenu and dispatch
InputHandler --> Mode : _mode controls which\noperations are shown
RUN_SESSION_NOTE ..> InputHandler : creates and calls run()

GuiCalculator --> Calculator : holds reference via\n_calculator
GuiCalculator --> History : manages session history
GuiCalculator --> Logger : logs errors via\n_logger
GuiCalculator *-- OperationDispatcher : owns _dispatcher
GuiCalculator *-- BaseMode : owns _mode_handler
GuiCalculator ..> OPERATIONS_NOTE : reads registry for\narity and coerce
GuiCalculator --> Mode : _mode controls which\noperations are shown

BaseMode ..> OPERATIONS_NOTE : reads OPERATIONS and\nNORMAL_OPERATIONS for\nfiltering logic
BaseMode --> Mode : filters based on Mode value

CliDispatcher --> Calculator : holds reference via\n_calculator
CliDispatcher --> Logger : logs errors via\n_logger
CliDispatcher *-- OperationDispatcher : owns _dispatcher
CliDispatcher ..> OPERATIONS_NOTE : reads registry for\narity and coerce
MAIN_NOTE ..> CliDispatcher : creates and calls\ndispatch_from_args()

@enduml
